---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Onboarding Quickstart" description="From local binary to first deploy on a clean server.">
  <h1>Onboarding Quickstart</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-2); font-size: 1.05rem;">
    Use this path for the zero-manual experience: install local CLI, bootstrap remote host, verify readiness, deploy.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Install local CLI</h2>
  <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://github.com/deep-thinking-llc/voxeltron/releases/latest/download/install-voxeltron.sh | bash</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Bootstrap a clean server</h2>
  <pre><code>voxeltron bootstrap root@203.0.113.10 \
  --domain apps.example.com \
  --email ops@example.com \
  --profile prod \
  --yes</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Verify health</h2>
  <pre><code>voxeltron doctor local
voxeltron doctor remote --server prod --domain apps.example.com</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Deploy first app</h2>
  <pre><code>voxeltron deploy nginx:alpine --name hello --server prod --wait</code></pre>

  <h2>JSON mode for automation</h2>
  <pre><code>voxeltron bootstrap root@203.0.113.10 --profile prod --yes --json
voxeltron deploy nginx --name hello --server prod --wait --json</code></pre>

